#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment.rst:58
msgid "Replenishment report and reordering rules"
msgstr "補貨報告及重新訂購規則"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment.rst:60
msgid ""
"Reordering rules are rules that can be set up to maintain a minimum stock "
"level. They are often configured to support manufacturing or sales "
"requirements. When a product's stock falls at or below the minimum level, "
"Odoo generates (or suggests) a purchase or manufacturing order to replenish "
"stock to the maximum level."
msgstr ""
"補貨規則是可以設定以維持最低庫存水準的規則。它們通常用於支援製造或銷售需求。"
"當產品庫存降至或低於最低水準時，Odoo\\ 會生成（或建議）採購單或製造單以補充庫"
"存至最高水準。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment.rst:65
msgid ""
"When using automatic reordering rules, Odoo generates a new order. When "
"using manual, Odoo suggests orders on the replenishment report. For detailed "
"guidance, refer to the :doc:`replenishment report <replenishment/report>` "
"and :doc:`reordering rules <replenishment/reordering_rules>`."
msgstr ""
"使用自動補貨規則時，Odoo\\ 會生成新訂單。使用手動時，Odoo\\ 會在補貨報表中建"
"議訂單。如需詳細指引，請參閱\\ :doc:`補貨報表 <replenishment/report>`\\ 和\\ "
":doc:`補貨規則 <replenishment/reordering_rules>`\\ 。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment.rst:69
msgid "Key points include:"
msgstr "關鍵要點包括："

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment.rst:71
msgid ""
":ref:`Automatic reordering rules <inventory/warehouses_storage/auto-rr>`: "
"Automatically create |POs| or |MOs| when stock falls below the minimum "
"level. While this is convenient, it is less flexible."
msgstr ""
":ref:`自動補貨規則 <inventory/warehouses_storage/auto-rr>`：當庫存低於最低水"
"準時自動建立\\ |POs|\\ 或\\ |MOs|\\ 。雖然這很方便，但彈性較低。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment.rst:74
msgid ""
":ref:`Manual reordering rules <inventory/warehouses_storage/manual-rr>`: "
"Generate suggestions in the replenishment report for user review, allowing "
"adjustments and batch orders while meeting deadlines."
msgstr ""
":ref:`手動補貨規則 <inventory/warehouses_storage/manual-rr>`：在補貨報表中生"
"成建議供使用者審查，允許調整和批次訂單，同時滿足截止日期。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment.rst:77
msgid ""
":doc:`Just in time logic <replenishment/just_in_time>`: A strategy to "
"replenish only what is needed to prevent overstocking."
msgstr ""
":doc:`準時制邏輯 <replenishment/just_in_time>`：一種僅補貨所需數量以防止庫存"
"過剩的策略。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment.rst:81
msgid ":doc:`replenishment/reordering_rules`"
msgstr ":doc:`replenishment/reordering_rules`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment.rst:82
msgid ":doc:`replenishment/report`"
msgstr ":doc:`replenishment/report`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment.rst:87
msgid "Make to order"
msgstr "按訂單生產"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment.rst:89
msgid ""
"An |MTO| strategy means that procurement or production is triggered only "
"after a sales order has been confirmed. This strategy is recommended when "
"products are customizable, demand is unpredictable, there is limited storage "
"capacity, and when products are high in value and low in demand. In such "
"cases, it does not make sense to keep on-hand inventory."
msgstr ""
"|MTO|\\ 策略意味著只有在銷售單確認後才會觸發採購或生產。當產品可客製化、需求"
"不可預測、儲存空間有限以及產品價值高但需求低時，建議採用此策略。在這種情況下"
"，保留現有庫存並不合理。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment.rst:94
msgid ""
"Unlike products replenished using reordering rules, Odoo automatically links "
"the sales order to the |PO| or |MO| generated by the |MTO| route."
msgstr ""
"與使用重新訂購規則補充的產品不同，Odoo 會自動將銷售訂單連結至由 |MTO| 路線生"
"成的 |PO| 或 |MO|。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment.rst:97
msgid ""
"Another difference between reordering rules and |MTO| is, with |MTO|, Odoo "
"generates a draft |PO| or |MO| immediately after the |SO| is confirmed. With "
"reordering rules, Odoo generates a draft |PO| or |MO| when the product's "
"forecasted stock falls below the set minimum quantity."
msgstr ""
"重新訂購規則與 |MTO| 的另一個分別是，使用 |MTO| 時，Odoo 會在確認 |SO| 後，立"
"即生成草稿 |PO| 或 |MO|。而使用重新訂購規則時，當產品的預測庫存低於設定的最小"
"數量時，Odoo 就會生成草稿 |PO| 或 |MO|。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment.rst:101
msgid ""
"In addition, Odoo automatically adds quantities to the |PO| or |MO| as the "
"forecast changes, so long as the |PO| or |MO| is not confirmed."
msgstr ""
"此外，只要 |PO| 或 |MO| 未確認，Odoo 會在預測發生變化時，自動將數量加入至 |"
"PO| 或 |MO| 中。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment.rst:104
msgid ""
"The |MTO| route is the best replenishment strategy for products that are "
"customized, and/or for products that have no stock kept on-hand."
msgstr "對於客製化產品及/或沒有庫存的產品， |MTO| 路線會是最佳的補貨策略。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment.rst:108
msgid ":doc:`replenishment/mto`"
msgstr ":doc:`replenishment/mto`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment.rst:111
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:3
msgid "Master production schedule"
msgstr "主生產計劃"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment.rst:113
msgid ""
"The :abbr:`MPS (Master Production Schedule)` is a dashboard where products "
"and their forecasted quantities are entered. Based on confirmed "
"manufacturing and purchase orders, the dashboard recommends amounts to order "
"or produce."
msgstr ""
":abbr:`MPS（主生產計劃）`\\ 是一個\\ Dashboard，可在其中輸入產品及其預測數量"
"。根據已確認的製造單和採購單，Dashboard\\ 會建議訂購或生產的數量。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment.rst:117
msgid ""
"This a useful **manual** tool for keeping track of quantities. "
"The :abbr:`MPS (Master Production Schedule)` **should absolutely not** be "
"used alongside reordering rules, as the automated workflow disrupts its "
"manual replenishment method."
msgstr ""
"這是一個有用的\\ **手動**\\ 工具，用於追蹤數量。:abbr:`MPS（主生產計劃）`\\ "
"**絕對不應**\\ 與補貨規則一起使用，因為自動化工作流程會破壞其手動補貨方法。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment.rst:122
msgid ":doc:`../../manufacturing/workflows/use_mps`"
msgstr ":doc:`../../manufacturing/workflows/use_mps`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:8
msgid ""
"*Just-in-time logic* in Odoo minimizes storage costs by placing orders "
"precisely to meet deadlines. This is achieved using the :ref:`forecasted "
"date <inventory/warehouses_storage/forecasted-date>`, which determines when "
"replenishment is necessary to avoid overstocking. For example, for a product "
"with a 5-day total lead time and a sales order delivery date in 10 days, "
"Odoo waits 5 days to place the order, ensuring it arrives just in time for "
"delivery."
msgstr ""
"Odoo 中的\\ *準時制邏輯*\\ 透過精確下單以符合截止日期，將儲存成本降至最低。這"
"是使用\\ :ref:`預測日期 <inventory/warehouses_storage/forecasted-date>`\\ 實"
"現的，該日期決定何時需要補貨以避免庫存過剩。例如，對於總前置時間為 5 天且銷售"
"單交貨日期為 10 天後的產品，Odoo 會等待 5 天再下單，確保準時送達以進行交貨。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:14
msgid ""
"The forecasted date is the **earliest possible date** to receive a product "
"if the replenishment process starts immediately. It is calculated by summing "
"the lead times linked to the replenishment process, such as :ref:`vendor "
"lead times <inventory/warehouses_storage/purchase-vendor-lt>` for purchases "
"or :ref:`manufacturing lead times <inventory/warehouses_storage/"
"manufacturing-lt>` for production. This works with both automatic and manual "
"reordering rules."
msgstr ""
"預測日期是指如果立即開始補貨流程，接收產品的**最早可能日期**。其計算方式為將"
"與補貨流程相關的前置時間相加，例如採購的\\ :ref:`供應商前置時間 <inventory/"
"warehouses_storage/purchase-vendor-lt>`\\ 或生產的\\ :ref:`製造前置時間 "
"<inventory/warehouses_storage/manufacturing-lt>`\\ 。此功能適用於自動和手動補"
"貨規則。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:21
msgid ""
"If utilizing just-in-time logic feels risky, consider adding buffer time "
"or :doc:`adjusting lead times <lead_times>` for more flexibility. While lead "
"times and just-in-time logic provide additional control, reordering rules "
"work perfectly fine without them. Keeping delivery dates on |SOs| as their "
"*creation date* ensures purchases are immediately triggered when needed."
msgstr ""
"如果使用準時制邏輯感覺有風險，請考慮加入緩衝時間或\\ :doc:`調整前置時間 "
"<lead_times>`\\ 以獲得更大彈性。雖然前置時間和準時制邏輯提供額外控制，但補貨"
"規則在沒有它們的情況下也能完美運作。將\\ |SOs|\\ 上的交貨日期保持為其\\ *建立"
"日期*\\ 可確保在需要時立即觸發採購。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:29
msgid "Forecasted date and to order quantity"
msgstr "預測日期和訂購數量"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:31
msgid ""
"The *forecasted date* is the earliest receipt date for a product, if it is "
"ordered right now. It is calculated by summing the lead times linked to the "
"product's replenishment process. The total of these lead times, added to the "
"current date, determines when Odoo checks for demanded stock."
msgstr ""
"*預測日期*是產品如果現在訂購的最早收貨日期。其計算方式是將與產品補貨流程連結"
"的前置時間總和相加。這些前置時間的總和加上目前日期，決定 Odoo 檢查所需庫存的"
"時間。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:35
msgid ""
"To view the forecasted date go to :menuselection:`Inventory app --> "
"Operations --> Replenishment` to access the :doc:`replenishment report "
"<report>`, then click the :icon:`fa-info-circle` :guilabel:`(info)` icon for "
"the desired reordering rule. The :guilabel:`Replenishment Information` pop-"
"up window displays the :guilabel:`Forecasted Date` and various lead times."
msgstr ""
"若要檢視預測日期，請前往\\ :menuselection:`庫存應用程式 --> 作業 --> 補貨`\\ "
"以存取\\ :doc:`補貨報告 <report>`，然後按一下所需補貨規則的\\ :icon:`fa-info-"
"circle`\\ :guilabel:`資訊`\\ 圖示。:guilabel:`補貨資訊`\\ 彈出視窗會顯示\\ "
":guilabel:`預測日期`\\ 和各種前置時間。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:40
msgid ""
"The just-in-time logic ensures replenishment occurs only when required to "
"meet forecasted demand, reducing the risk of overstocking."
msgstr "準時制邏輯確保僅在需要滿足預測需求時才進行補貨，降低庫存過剩的風險。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:44
msgid ""
"Just-in-time logic determines the exact timing of replenishment. If you want "
"to extend this logic to also consider near-future demand beyond the forecast "
"date, see :ref:`Horizon Days <inventory/warehouses_storage/horizon-days>`"
msgstr ""
"準時制邏輯決定補貨的確切時機。如果您想擴展此邏輯以考慮超出預測日期的近期需求"
"，請參閱\\ :ref:`天數範圍 <inventory/warehouses_storage/horizon-days>`。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:48
msgid ""
"If the forecasted quantity falls below the minimum on the forecasted date, "
"replenishment is triggered immediately to prevent shortages. If the quantity "
"falls below the minimum after the forecasted date, replenishment is deferred."
msgstr ""
"如果預測數量在預測日期低於最低值，則會立即觸發補貨以防止短缺。如果數量在預測"
"日期之後低於最低值，則會延遲補貨。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:52
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`To Order` quantity is defined as the total demand on the "
"forecasted date."
msgstr ":guilabel:`訂購`\\ 數量定義為預測日期的總需求。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:54
msgid ""
"By scheduling purchase orders according to combined lead times, Odoo "
"minimizes inventory while ensuring that future demand is met on time."
msgstr ""
"透過根據合併的前置時間安排採購單，Odoo 將庫存降至最低，同時確保準時滿足未來需"
"求。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:58
msgid ""
"A manual reordering rule is set up with no minimum or maximum quantities."
msgstr "設定手動補貨規則時不設定最小或最大數量。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:60
msgid "Vendor lead time is 4 days, and the days to purchase is 2 days."
msgstr "供應商前置時間為 4 天，採購天數為 2 天。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:61
msgid "Today's date is October 2."
msgstr "今天的日期是 10 月 2 日。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:62
msgid "These add up to 6 days, making the forecasted date, October 8."
msgstr "這些加起來是 6 天，使預測日期為 10 月 8 日。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:64
msgid ""
"A confirmed |SO| for 5 units has a delivery date of October 8th (6 days from "
"today). This demand will appear on the replenishment report today, in "
"the :guilabel:`To Order` field."
msgstr ""
"一張已確認的 5 個單位的\\ |SO|\\ 交貨日期為 10 月 8 日（從今天起 6 天）。此需"
"求將在今天的補貨報告中出現，位於\\ :guilabel:`訂購`\\ 欄位中。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:67
msgid ""
"However, if the delivery date were later than October 8th, it would not yet "
"appear on the report. Odoo only displays quantities to replenish when they "
"fall within the forecasted date window, ensuring orders are placed precisely "
"when needed."
msgstr ""
"但是，如果交貨日期晚於 10 月 8 日，則尚不會出現在報告中。Odoo 僅在數量落在預"
"測日期視窗內時顯示要補貨的數量，確保在需要時精確下單。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:0
msgid "Show forecasted date in Odoo."
msgstr "在 Odoo 中顯示預測日期。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:75
msgid ""
"|SOs| scheduled after the :guilabel:`Forecasted Date` are not included in "
"the :guilabel:`Forecast` quantities of a reordering rule. However, they do "
"appear in the forecasted report, since it reflects the long-term forecasted "
"quantity. To access the forecasted report, click :icon:`fa-area-"
"chart` :guilabel:`(area chart)` icon on the replenishment report."
msgstr ""
"在\\ :guilabel:`預測日期`\\ 之後排程的\\ |SOs|\\ 不包含在補貨規則的\\ "
":guilabel:`預測`\\ 數量中。但是，它們會出現在預測報告中，因為該報告反映長期預"
"測數量。若要存取預測報告，請按一下補貨報告上的\\ :icon:`fa-area-chart`\\ "
":guilabel:`區域圖`\\ 圖示。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:81
msgid ":doc:`Reordering Rules <reordering_rules>`"
msgstr ":doc:`補貨規則 <reordering_rules>`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:82
msgid ":doc:`Replenishment Report <report>`"
msgstr ":doc:`補貨報告 <report>`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/just_in_time.rst:83
msgid ":doc:`Lead Times <lead_times>`"
msgstr ":doc:`前置時間 <lead_times>`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:3
msgid "Lead times"
msgstr "交貨需時"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:13
msgid ""
"Accurate delivery date forecasting is essential for customer satisfaction. "
"The **Inventory** app provides comprehensive lead time configuration "
"settings to improve the coordination and planning of manufacturing orders, "
"deliveries, and receipts."
msgstr ""
"準確的交貨日期預測對於客戶滿意度至關重要。**庫存**應用程式提供全面的前置時間"
"配置設定，以改善製造單、交貨和收貨的協調與規劃。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:18
msgid "Types of lead times"
msgstr "前置時間的類型"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:20
msgid ""
"Different lead times for different operations can impact various stages of "
"the order fulfillment process. The following lead times can be configured in "
"Odoo:"
msgstr ""
"不同作業的不同前置時間可能會影響訂單履行流程的各個階段。在 Odoo 中可以配置以"
"下前置時間："

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:None
msgid ""
"A diagram breaking down the different types of lead times in the fulfillment "
"process."
msgstr "分解履行流程中不同前置時間類型的圖表。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:26
msgid ""
":ref:`Customer lead time <inventory/warehouses_storage/sales-customer-lt>`: "
"The number of days from the sales order (SO) confirmation date and the date "
"the order is shipped from the warehouse. This is the expected time frame for "
"customer order fulfillment, also known as *delivery lead time*."
msgstr ""
":ref:`客戶前置時間 <inventory/warehouses_storage/sales-customer-lt>`\\ ：從銷"
"售單確認日期到訂單從倉庫出貨日期之間的天數。這是客戶訂單履行的預期時間範圍，"
"也稱為*交貨前置時間*。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:31
msgid ""
":ref:`Sales security lead time <inventory/warehouses_storage/sales-security-"
"lt>`: Moves the *scheduled delivery date* forward by a specified number of "
"days. This serves as a buffer to account for potential delays in the "
"fulfillment process and ensures ample time to prepare the outgoing shipment."
msgstr ""
":ref:`銷售安全前置時間 <inventory/warehouses_storage/sales-security-lt>`\\ ："
"將*預定交貨日期*提前指定的天數。這可作為緩衝，以應對履行流程中可能出現的延遲"
"，並確保有充足的時間準備出貨。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:36
msgid ""
":ref:`Shipping policy lead time <inventory/warehouses_storage/sales-shipping-"
"policy-lt>`: The shipping policy lead time determines how the scheduled "
"delivery date is set for orders with multiple products, based on the lead "
"times of the products in the order. This provides flexibility to choose "
"between multiple shipments delivered as soon as products are ready, or one "
"consolidated shipment when all products are ready."
msgstr ""
":ref:`出貨政策前置時間 <inventory/warehouses_storage/sales-shipping-policy-"
"lt>`\\ ：出貨政策前置時間決定如何根據訂單中產品的前置時間，為包含多個產品的訂"
"單設定預定交貨日期。這提供了靈活性，可以選擇在產品準備好後立即進行多次出貨，"
"或在所有產品都準備好時進行一次合併出貨。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:42
msgid ""
":ref:`Manufacturing lead time <inventory/warehouses_storage/manufacturing-"
"lt>`: The number of days needed to complete a manufacturing order (MO) from "
"the date of confirmation, including weekends (non-working hours in Odoo). "
"This is used to forecast an approximate production date for a finished good."
msgstr ""
":ref:`製造前置時間 <inventory/warehouses_storage/manufacturing-lt>`\\ ：從確"
"認日期起完成製造單所需的天數，包括週末（Odoo 中的非工作時間）。此用於預測成品"
"的大約生產日期。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:47
msgid ""
":ref:`Days to prepare manufacturing order <inventory/warehouses_storage/days-"
"to-prepare-mo-lt>`: The number of days needed to replenish components, or "
"manufacture sub-assemblies of the product. Either set one directly on the "
"bill of materials (BoM), or click *Compute* to sum up purchase and "
"manufacturing lead times of components in the |BoM|."
msgstr ""
":ref:`準備製造單所需天數 <inventory/warehouses_storage/days-to-prepare-mo-lt>"
"`\\ ：補充零件或製造產品子組件所需的天數。可直接在物料清單上設定一個，或按一"
"下*計算*以加總\\ |BoM|\\ 中零件的採購和製造前置時間。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:52
msgid ""
":ref:`Vendor lead time <inventory/warehouses_storage/purchase-vendor-lt>`: "
"The number of days from the confirmation of a purchase order (PO) to the "
"receipt of products. This provides insight on the time it takes for products "
"to arrive at the warehouse, facilitating effective scheduling and planning "
"of supplier deliveries."
msgstr ""
":ref:`供應商前置時間 <inventory/warehouses_storage/purchase-vendor-lt>`\\ ："
"從確認採購單到收到產品之間的天數。這可提供產品到達倉庫所需時間的洞察，有助於"
"有效安排和規劃供應商交貨。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:57
msgid ""
":ref:`Days to purchase <inventory/warehouses_storage/days-to-purchase-lt>`: "
"The number of days needed for the vendor to receive a request for quotation "
"(RFQ) and confirm it. This advances the deadline to schedule a |RFQ| by a "
"specified number of days."
msgstr ""
":ref:`採購所需天數 <inventory/warehouses_storage/days-to-purchase-lt>`\\ ：供"
"應商接收報價請求並確認所需的天數。這會將安排\\ |RFQ|\\ 的截止日期提前指定的天"
"數。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:62
msgid ""
"Lead times are calculated in the order provided above, working backward from "
"the delivery deadline using :doc:`just-in-time (JIT) logic <just_in_time>`."
msgstr ""
"前置時間的計算順序如上所示，使用\\ :doc:`準時制（JIT）邏輯 <just_in_time>`\\ "
"從交貨截止日期向後計算。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:65
msgid ""
"The manual replenishment timeline can be further extended by increasing the "
"forecasted date on the replenishment report. See :ref:`horizon days "
"<inventory/warehouses_storage/horizon-days>` to learn more."
msgstr ""
"可透過增加補貨報告上的預測日期來進一步延長手動補貨時間表。請參閱\\ :ref:`預測"
"天數 <inventory/warehouses_storage/horizon-days>`\\ 以瞭解更多資訊。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:72
msgid "Sales lead times"
msgstr "銷售前置時間"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:74
msgid ""
"*Customer lead times* and *sales security lead times* can be configured to "
"automatically compute an *expected delivery date* on a :abbr:`SO (Sales "
"Order)`. The expected delivery date ensures a realistic *delivery dates* "
"setting for shipments from the warehouse."
msgstr ""
"*客戶前置時間*和*銷售安全前置時間*可以配置為自動計算\\ :abbr:`銷售單`\\ 上"
"的*預期交貨日期*。預期交貨日期可確保從倉庫出貨的*交貨日期*設定切合實際。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:78
msgid ""
"Odoo issues a warning message if the set delivery date is earlier than the "
"expected date, as it may not be feasible to fulfill the order by that time, "
"which would impact other warehouse operations."
msgstr ""
"如果設定的交付日期早於預期日期，Odoo\\ 會發出警告訊息，因為可能無法在該時間前"
"完成訂單，這會影響其他倉庫作業。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:82
msgid ""
"A :abbr:`SO (sales order)` containing a `Coconut-scented candle` is "
"confirmed on March 4. The product has a customer lead time of 14 days, and "
"the business uses a sales security lead time of 1 day. Based on the lead "
"time inputs, Odoo suggests a delivery date in 15 days, on March 19."
msgstr ""
":abbr:`SO（銷售單）`包含一個 `椰子香氛蠟燭` 產品，在 3 月 4 日確認。該產品的"
"客戶交貨時間為 14 天，企業使用 1 天的銷售安全交貨時間。根據交貨時間輸入，"
"Odoo 建議在 15 天後的 3 月 19 日交貨。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:0
msgid ""
"Set Delivery Date in a sales order. Enables delivery lead times feature."
msgstr "在銷售單中設定交貨日期。啟用交貨時間功能。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:92
msgid "Customer lead time"
msgstr "客戶前置時間"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:94
msgid ""
"The *customer lead time* is manually assigned for each individual product. "
"To set the customer lead time for a product, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Sales app --> Products --> Products`. Select the desired "
"product, and switch to the :guilabel:`Inventory` tab. In "
"the :guilabel:`Customer Lead Time` field, enter the number of calendar days "
"required to fulfill the delivery order from start to finish."
msgstr ""
"*客戶交貨時間*需為每個產品手動指定。要設定產品的客戶交貨時間，前往\\ "
":menuselection:`銷售應用程式 --> 產品 --> 產品`\\ 。選擇所需產品，然後切換"
"到\\ :guilabel:`庫存`\\ 分頁。在\\ :guilabel:`客戶交貨時間`\\ 欄位中，輸入從"
"開始到完成履行交貨訂單所需的日曆天數。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:101
msgid ""
"Set a 14-day customer lead time for the `Coconut-scented candle` by "
"navigating to its product form. Then, in the :guilabel:`Inventory` tab, type "
"`14.00` days into the :guilabel:`Customer Lead Time` field."
msgstr ""
"透過導航至\\ `Coconut-scented candle`\\ 的產品表單，為其設定\\ 14\\ 天的客戶"
"前置時間。然後，在\\ :guilabel:`庫存`\\ 分頁中，在\\ :guilabel:`客戶前置時"
"間`\\ 欄位中輸入\\ `14.00`\\ 天。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:0
msgid "Assign a Customer Lead Time in the product form."
msgstr "在產品表單中指定客戶交貨時間。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:111
msgid "Sales security lead time"
msgstr "銷售安全前置時間"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:113
msgid ""
"The *sales security lead time* applies to all sales orders for the company. "
"To set the sales security lead time, navigate to :menuselection:`Inventory "
"app --> Configuration --> Settings`, and scroll down to "
"the :guilabel:`Advanced Scheduling` section near the end of the page. Check "
"the box for :guilabel:`Security Lead Time for Sales` to enable the feature."
msgstr ""
"*銷售安全交貨時間*適用於公司的所有銷售單。要設定銷售安全交貨時間，前往\\ "
":menuselection:`庫存應用程式 --> 配置 --> 設定`\\ ，然後向下捲動到頁面末尾附"
"近的\\ :guilabel:`進階排程`\\ 區段。勾選\\ :guilabel:`銷售安全交貨時間`\\ 方"
"塊以啟用此功能。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:118
msgid ""
"Next, enter the desired number of calendar days. This security lead time is "
"a buffer notifying the team to prepare for outgoing shipments earlier than "
"the scheduled date."
msgstr ""
"接下來，輸入所需的日曆天數。此安全前置時間是一個緩衝區，通知團隊比預定日期更"
"早準備出貨。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:122
msgid ""
"Setting the :guilabel:`Security Lead Time for Sales` to `1.00` day, pushes "
"the :guilabel:`Scheduled Date` of a delivery order (DO) forward by one day. "
"In that case, if a product is initially scheduled for delivery on April 6th, "
"but with a one-day security lead time, the new scheduled date for the "
"delivery order would be April 5th."
msgstr ""
"將\\ :guilabel:`銷售安全前置時間`\\ 設定為\\ `1.00`\\ 天，會將交貨單（DO）"
"的\\ :guilabel:`計劃日期`\\ 提前一天。在這種情況下，如果產品最初計劃於\\ 4\\ "
"月\\ 6\\ 日交付，但由於有一天的安全前置時間，交貨單的新計劃日期將是\\ 4\\ "
"月\\ 5\\ 日。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:0
msgid ""
"View of the security lead time for sales configuration from the sales "
"settings."
msgstr "從銷售設定檢視銷售安全前置時間配置。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:133
msgid "Shipping policy"
msgstr "運送政策"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:135
msgid ""
"For orders that include multiple products with different lead times, the "
"lead times can be configured directly from the quotation itself. On a "
"quotation, click the :guilabel:`Other Info` tab and set "
"the :guilabel:`Shipping Policy` field."
msgstr ""
"對於包含多個具有不同交貨時間的產品的訂單，可以直接從報價單本身配置交貨時間。"
"在報價單上，按一下\\ :guilabel:`其他資訊`\\ 分頁並設定\\ :guilabel:`運送政"
"策`\\ 欄位。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:139
msgid ""
":guilabel:`As soon as possible`: Deliver products as soon as they are ready. "
"The :guilabel:`Scheduled Date` of the :abbr:`DO (Delivery Order)` is "
"determined by adding today's date to the shortest lead time among the "
"products in the order."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`盡快`：產品準備好後立即交貨。:guilabel:`排定日期`\\ 的\\ :abbr:`DO"
"（交貨單）`\\ 是透過將今天的日期加上訂單中產品的最短交貨時間來決定。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:143
msgid ""
":guilabel:`When all products are ready` to wait to fulfill the entire order "
"at once. The :guilabel:`Scheduled Date` of the :abbr:`DO (Delivery Order)` "
"is determined by adding today's date to the longest lead time among the "
"products in the order."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`所有產品均已就緒`，等待一次完成整個訂單。:guilabel:`預定日期`的\\ "
":abbr:`交貨單`\\ 是透過將今天的日期加上訂單中產品的最長前置時間來決定。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:None
msgid "Show *Shipping Policy* field in the *Other Info* tab of a quotation."
msgstr "在報價單的\\ *其他資訊*\\ 分頁中顯示\\ *運送政策*\\ 欄位。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:151
msgid ""
"In a quotation containing 2 products, `Yoga mat` and `Resistance band,` the "
"products have a lead time of 8 days and 5 days, respectively. Today's date "
"is April 2nd."
msgstr ""
"在包含 2 個產品的報價單中，`瑜伽墊`\\ 和\\ `阻力帶`\\ 的前置時間分別為 8 天"
"和 5 天。今天的日期是 4 月 2 日。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:154
msgid ""
"When the :guilabel:`Shipping Policy` is set to :guilabel:`As soon as "
"possible`, the scheduled delivery date is 5 days from today: April 7th. On "
"the other hand, selecting :guilabel:`When all products are ready` configures "
"the scheduled date to be 8 days from today: April 10th."
msgstr ""
"當\\ :guilabel:`運送政策`\\ 設定為\\ :guilabel:`儘快`\\ 時，預定交貨日期為距"
"今 5 天：4 月 7 日。另一方面，選擇\\ :guilabel:`所有產品均已就緒`\\ 會將預定"
"日期配置為距今 8 天：4 月 10 日。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:161
msgid "Manufacturing lead times"
msgstr "製造前置時間"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:163
msgid ""
"Lead times can help simplify the procurement process for consumable "
"materials and components used in manufactured products with bills of "
"materials (BoMs)."
msgstr ""
"交貨期可協助簡化已製造產品的可耗用物料和零組件的採購流程，這些產品具有物料清"
"單（BoMs）。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:166
msgid ""
"The |MO| deadline, which is the deadline to begin the manufacturing process "
"to complete the product by the scheduled delivery date, can be determined by "
"configuring the manufacturing lead times and manufacturing security lead "
"times."
msgstr ""
"製造訂單截止日期（即在預定交貨日期前完成產品的製造流程開始截止日期）可透過設"
"定製造交貨期和製造安全交貨期來決定。|MO|"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:None
msgid ""
"Visualization of the determination of planned MO date manufacturing lead "
"times."
msgstr "以視覺化方式呈現規劃製造訂單日期製造交貨期的確定方式。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:176
msgid "Manufacturing lead time"
msgstr "製造交貨期"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:178
msgid ""
"Manufacturing lead times for products are configured from a product's bill "
"of materials (BoM) form."
msgstr "產品的製造交貨期從產品的物料清單（BoM）表單設定。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:180
msgid ""
"To add a lead time to a |BoM|, navigate to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app "
"--> Products --> Bills of Materials`, and select the desired |BoM| to edit."
msgstr ""
"如需將交貨期加入\\ |BoM|，請前往\\ :menuselection:`製造應用程式 --> 產品 --> "
"物料清單`，並選取所需的\\ |BoM|\\ 進行編輯。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:183
msgid ""
"On the |BoM| form, click the :guilabel:`Miscellaneous` tab. Change the value "
"(in days) in the :guilabel:`Manuf. Lead Time` field to specify the calendar "
"days needed to manufacture the product."
msgstr ""
"在\\ |BoM|\\ 表單上，按一下\\ :guilabel:`雜項`\\ 分頁。變更\\ :guilabel:`製造"
"交貨期`\\ 欄位中的值（以天數為單位），以指定製造產品所需的日曆天數。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:None
msgid "Manuf. Lead Time value specified on a product's Bill of Material form."
msgstr "在產品的物料清單表單上指定的製造交貨期值。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:190
msgid ""
"If the selected |BoM| is a multi-level |BoM|, the manufacturing lead times "
"of the components are added."
msgstr "如果選取的\\ |BoM|\\ 是多階\\ |BoM|，則會加總零組件的製造交貨期。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:193
msgid ""
"If the |BoM| product is subcontracted, the :guilabel:`Manuf. Lead Time` can "
"be used to determine the date at which components should be sent to the "
"subcontractor."
msgstr ""
"如果\\ |BoM|\\ 產品是委外加工的，則\\ :guilabel:`製造交貨期`\\ 可用於決定應將"
"零組件傳送給委外加工廠的日期。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:196
msgid ""
"Establish a |MO| deadline, based on the *expected delivery date*, indicated "
"in the :guilabel:`Scheduled Date` field of the :abbr:`DO (Delivery Order)`."
msgstr ""
"根據交貨單:abbr:`DO（Delivery Order）`的\\ :guilabel:`排程日期`\\ 欄位所示"
"的*預期交貨日期*，建立\\ |MO|\\ 截止日期。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:199
msgid ""
"The |MO| deadline, which is the :guilabel:`Scheduled Date` field on the |"
"MO|, is calculated as the *expected delivery date* subtracted by the "
"manufacturing lead time."
msgstr ""
"|MO|\\ 截止日期是\\ |MO|\\ 上的\\ :guilabel:`排程日期`\\ 欄位，其計算方式"
"為*預期交貨日期*減去製造交貨期。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:202
msgid ""
"This ensures the manufacturing process begins on time, in order to meet the "
"delivery date."
msgstr "這可確保製造流程準時開始，以符合交貨日期。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:204
msgid ""
"However, it is important to note that lead times are based on calendar days. "
"Lead times do **not** consider weekends, holidays, or *work center capacity* "
"(:dfn:`the number of operations that can be performed at the work center "
"simultaneously`)."
msgstr ""
"但請務必注意，交貨期是以日曆天數為基礎。交貨期**不會**考慮週末、假日或*工作中"
"心產能*（:dfn:`可在工作中心同時執行的作業數`）。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:209
msgid ""
":doc:`Manufacturing planning <../../../manufacturing/workflows/use_mps>`"
msgstr ":doc:`製造規劃 <../../../manufacturing/workflows/use_mps>`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:210
msgid ":doc:`Schedule MOs with reordering rules <reordering_rules>`"
msgstr ":doc:`使用重新訂購規則排程製造訂單 <reordering_rules>`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:213
msgid ""
"A product's scheduled shipment date on the :abbr:`DO (Delivery Order)` is "
"August 15th. The product requires 14 days to manufacture. So, the latest "
"date to start the :abbr:`MO (Manufacturing Order)` to meet the commitment "
"date is August 1st."
msgstr ""
"產品在交貨單:abbr:`DO（Delivery Order）`上的排程出貨日期為8月15日。該產品需要"
"14天進行製造。因此，為符合承諾日期而開始製造訂單:abbr:`MO（Manufacturing "
"Order）`的最晚日期為8月1日。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:220
msgid "Days to prepare manufacturing order"
msgstr "準備製造訂單的天數"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:222
msgid ""
"Configuring the days required to gather the components for a manufactured "
"product ensures there is enough time to either replenish components or "
"manufacture semi-finished products. This can be used as an extra figure to "
"cross-check and confirm that the order can be completed within the customer "
"lead time."
msgstr ""
"配置為製造產品收集元件所需的天數，可確保有足夠的時間來補充元件或製造半成品。"
"這可以用作額外數據來交叉檢查並確認訂單可以在客戶交貨時間內完成。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:227
msgid ""
"Go to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Products --> Bills of Materials` "
"and select the desired |BoM|. In the :guilabel:`Miscellaneous` tab of the |"
"BoM|, specify the calendar days needed to obtain components of the product "
"in the :guilabel:`Days to prepare Manufacturing Order` field, or "
"click :guilabel:`Compute` next to the :guilabel:`Days to prepare "
"Manufacturing Order` field to automatically fill in the longest lead time "
"among all the components listed on the |BoM|."
msgstr ""
"前往\\ :menuselection:`製造應用程式 --> 產品 --> 物料清單`\\ 並選擇所需的\\ "
"|BoM|\\ 。在\\ |BoM|\\ 的\\ :guilabel:`雜項`\\ 分頁中，在\\ :guilabel:`準備製"
"造訂單天數`\\ 欄位中指定取得產品元件所需的日曆天數，或按一下\\ :guilabel:`準"
"備製造訂單天數`\\ 欄位旁邊的\\ :guilabel:`計算`\\ 以自動填入\\ |BoM|\\ 上列出"
"的所有元件中最長的交貨時間。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:234
msgid ""
"A |BoM| has two components: one has a manufacturing lead time of two days, "
"and the other has a purchase lead time of four days. The :guilabel:`Days to "
"prepare Manufacturing Order` is four days."
msgstr ""
"一個\\ |BoM|\\ 有兩個元件：一個具有兩天的製造交貨時間，另一個具有四天的採購交"
"貨時間。:guilabel:`準備製造訂單天數`\\ 為四天。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:241
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:266
msgid "Purchase lead times"
msgstr "採購前置時間"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:243
msgid ""
"Automatically scheduling supplier orders streamlines procurement by showing "
"users exactly when to confirm a request for quotation (RFQ) and when to "
"expect the goods."
msgstr ""
"自動排程供應商訂單可簡化採購流程，向使用者明確顯示何時確認報價請求（RFQ）以及"
"何時預期收到貨物。"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times.rst:246
